This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a novel approach for learning values directly from observations. It also involves Reinforcement Learning (RL), which is a common topic in the Machine Learning community. 

It could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it involves learning from expert demonstrations and developing approaches for RL. 

The paper also involves computer vision techniques for processing visual information, which suggests it could belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision). 

Additionally, the use of RL for robotics applications suggests it could belong to cs.RO (Robotics). 

Finally, the paper involves learning values for decision-making, which could also place it in the sub-category of cs.SY (Systems and Control).
